file.name: Billing Entries
file.description: A dataset containing information about billing entries for legal matters handled by a law firm. Each record represents a single billing entry with details about the associated matter, attorney, hours worked, billing rate, and description of the work done.

columns.name: entry_id
columns.description: Unique identifier for the billing entry

columns.name: file_id
columns.description: Identifier for the legal matter or file associated with the billing entry

columns.name: att_id
columns.description: Identifier for the attorney associated with the billing entry

columns.name: hours
columns.description: Number of hours worked by the attorney for the billing entry

columns.name: rate
columns.description: Billing rate per hour for the attorney

columns.name: amount
columns.description: Total amount billed for the entry, calculated as hours worked times the billing rate

columns.name: description
columns.description: Brief description of the work done for the billing entry

columns.name: entry_date
columns.description: Date when the billing entry was made, in various formats (DD/MM/YY, YYYY-MM-DD, Unix timestamp)

file.name: Legal Dataset
file.description: A comprehensive dataset containing various legal-related files including client information, matters, billing entries, emails, documents, filings, and regulations. The dataset is heterogeneous, incorporating different file formats such as CSV, JSON, JSONL, TXT, and XML, and is designed to require entity resolution and mapping due to intentionally inconsistent IDs across files.

columns.name: files.billing_entries_A.csv.path
columns.description: Path to the billing entries file in CSV format, containing financial transaction records related to legal matters.

columns.name: files.document_metadata.json.path
columns.description: Path to the document metadata file in JSON format, providing information about the documents such as their type, creation date, and author.

columns.name: files.documents/D-2000_pdf.txt.path
columns.description: Path to a specific document file in TXT format, representing a document related to a legal matter or client.

columns.name: files.emails_A.jsonl.path
columns.description: Path to the emails file in JSONL format, containing email communications related to legal matters or clients.

columns.name: files.matters_A.csv.path
columns.description: Path to the matters file in CSV format, containing information about legal matters such as their status, type, and associated clients.

columns.name: files.regulations/REG-300.txt.path
columns.description: Path to a specific regulation file in TXT format, providing details about a particular legal regulation or law.

columns.name: files.structured_clients_A.csv.path
columns.description: Path to the structured clients file in CSV format, containing organized client information such as their name, address, and contact details.

file.name: Email Records
file.description: A dataset containing information about email communications, likely from a professional services firm. Each record represents a single email with details about the sender, recipients, subject, content, and any associated case or matter references.

columns.description: Unique identifier for the email

columns.name: from
columns.description: Email address of the sender

columns.name: to
columns.description: Email address of the primary recipient

columns.name: cc
columns.description: Email address(es) of secondary recipients (carbon copy)

columns.name: subject
columns.description: Subject line of the email

columns.name: timestamp
columns.description: Date and/or time the email was sent, in varying formats (DD-MMM-YYYY, YYYY-MM-DD, Unix timestamp, DD/MM/YY)

columns.name: body
columns.description: Content or body of the email
columns.example: Heads up: regulator issued a guidance yesterday.

columns.name: case_id_ref
columns.description: Reference to an associated case or matter identifier, if applicable

file.name: Legal Matters
file.description: A dataset containing information about legal matters or cases handled by a law firm. Each record represents a single legal matter with details about the case, client, practice area, assigned attorney, and case value. The dataset covers various practice areas, including Intellectual Property (IP), Regulatory, and Employment, indicating a diverse range of legal services provided to clients.

columns.name: client_ref

columns.name: practice_area
columns.description: Area of law or legal practice associated with the matter (e.g., IP, Regulatory, Employment)

columns.name: opened_on
columns.description: Date when the legal matter was opened, with varying formats (DD/MM/YY, DD MMM YYYY, YYYY-MM-DD)

columns.name: lead_attorney

columns.name: estimated_value
